cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their application in image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new pooling operator that can be learned, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the benefits of the proposed method in terms of generalization and robustness, which are important topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also mentions experiments on datasets, which could fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL) but is less likely compared to the other categories mentioned.
